metadata.name: AIRDROPS
metadata.comment: Records of all transfers on Osmosis, including IBC transfers as on- and off-ramps to Osmosis and wallet to wallet transfers

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TRANSFER_TYPE.name: TRANSFER_TYPE
TRANSFER_TYPE.comment: Details on the type of transfer occurring during the transaction. "IBC_Transfer_In" = depositing tokens onto Osmosis. "IBC_transfer_out" = withdrawing tokens from Osmosis. "Osmosis" = wallet to wallet transfer on Osmosis.

SENDER.name: SENDER
SENDER.comment: The wallet address of the individual sent tokens in the transfer.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

RECEIVER.name: RECEIVER
RECEIVER.comment: The wallet address of the individual received tokens in the transfer.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

metadata.name: EZ_REDBANK_BALANCE_CHANGES
metadata.comment: Records of all balance change actions that occured within MARS red bank on osmosis

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Value grouping different messages together to represent a single action. Format will include the numeric msg_group and msg_sub_group with a ":" seperator. The subgroup will always be 0 except for "Exec" actions. NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_SUB_GROUP.name: MSG_SUB_GROUP
MSG_SUB_GROUP.comment: Silver only -- Numeric value grouping different messages together to represent a single action within a group. This is relevent for exec actions that contain mutiple underlying actions. NULL sub group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_INDEX.name: MSG_INDEX
MSG_INDEX.comment: Short for "message index," the position in which messages occur in a transaction.

CONTRACT_NAME.name: CONTRACT_NAME
CONTRACT_NAME.comment: The name of the contract that was interacted with

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment: The action that took place in the transaction. This always be balance_change.

USER.name: USER
USER.comment: The address that the balance change is relevant for

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

REWARDS_ACCRUED.name: REWARDS_ACCRUED
REWARDS_ACCRUED.comment: The amount of rewards that have accured

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was sent to the Flipside database.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

LIQUIDITY_PROVIDER_ADDRESS.name: LIQUIDITY_PROVIDER_ADDRESS
LIQUIDITY_PROVIDER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of user that provided or removed liquidity from the pool.

metadata.name: LOCKED_LIQUIDITY_ACTIONS
metadata.comment: Records of all LP token locking transactions that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. These actions include lock, unlock, unpool, and all superfluid actions.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Value grouping different messages together to represent a single action. Format will include the numeric msg_group and msg_sub_group with a ":" seperator. The subgroup will always be 0 except for "Exec" actions. NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_TYPE.name: MSG_TYPE
MSG_TYPE.comment: A string containing information about the type of message occurring.

MSG_ACTION.name: MSG_ACTION
MSG_ACTION.comment:
<<<<<<< HEAD
Tells what action is happening in the transaction. I.E. is the user adding or removing liquidity to the pool. 
=======
The action taken in the msg group. For staking this includes delegate, undelegate, redelegate, withdraw_rewards.
>>>>>>> main

MSG_ACTION_DESCRIPTION.name: MSG_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
MSG_ACTION_DESCRIPTION.comment: A user friendly description of what action occured

LOCKER_ADDRESS.name: LOCKER_ADDRESS
LOCKER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of user that performed an action related to locked lp tokens

LOCK_ID.name: LOCK_ID
LOCK_ID.comment: The unique id related to the specifc address, pool, and lock duration

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

POOL_ID.name: POOL_ID
POOL_ID.comment: Identifier for the pool within the module

LOCK_DURATION.name: LOCK_DURATION
LOCK_DURATION.comment: The length of time the LP toke takes to unlock

UNLOCK_TIME.name: UNLOCK_TIME
UNLOCK_TIME.comment: When the LP token is fully unlocked and liquid again

IS_SUPERFLUID.name: IS_SUPERFLUID
IS_SUPERFLUID.comment: The length of time the LP toke takes to unlock

UNPOOL_NEW_LOCK_IDS.name: UNPOOL_NEW_LOCK_IDS
UNPOOL_NEW_LOCK_IDS.comment: The new lock ids generated when a lp position is unpooled

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

metadata.name: FACT_MSG_ATTRIBUTES
metadata.comment: Records of all message attributes associated to messages that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. The columns blockchain and chain_id will be deprecating soon.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Value grouping different messages together to represent a single action. Format will include the numeric msg_group and msg_sub_group with a ":" seperator. The subgroup will always be 0 except for "Exec" actions. NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_INDEX.name: MSG_INDEX
MSG_INDEX.comment: Short for "message index," the position in which messages occur in a transaction.

MSG_TYPE.name: MSG_TYPE
MSG_TYPE.comment: A string containing information about the type of message occurring.

ATTRIBUTE_KEY.name: ATTRIBUTE_KEY
ATTRIBUTE_KEY.comment: They key from the key-value pair from the message attribute

ATTRIBUTE_VALUE.name: ATTRIBUTE_VALUE
ATTRIBUTE_VALUE.comment: They value from the key-value pair from the message attribute

ADDRESS.name: ADDRESS
ADDRESS.comment: Address unique to an individual wallet, validator, or token.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: In this table, always Osmosis. Used to join to cross-chain tables. This column will deprecate in all tables except core.fact_blocks soon. Please modify your queries to join to the blocks table to use this field.

CREATOR.name: CREATOR
CREATOR.comment: Name of the label creator - for now, this will always be "Flipside."

LABEL_TYPE.name: LABEL_TYPE
LABEL_TYPE.comment: A broad category that describes what a label is representing.

LABEL_SUBTYPE.name: LABEL_SUBTYPE
LABEL_SUBTYPE.comment: Adds more detail to the label type.

LABEL.name: LABEL
LABEL.comment: The label or name of the address.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the project the label belongs to.

ACCOUNT_ADDRESS.name: ACCOUNT_ADDRESS
ACCOUNT_ADDRESS.comment: The osmosis address of the user / entity that operates the validator.

DELEGATOR_SHARES.name: DELEGATOR_SHARES
DELEGATOR_SHARES.comment: The number of tokens staked to the validator.

JAILED.name: JAILED
JAILED.comment: FALSE when a validator is not jailed, TRUE when a validator is jailed

MAX_CHANGE_RATE.name: MAX_CHANGE_RATE
MAX_CHANGE_RATE.comment: The maximum rate at which a validator can change their commission per day.

MAX_RATE.name: MAX_RATE
MAX_RATE.comment: The maximum commission rate that the validator can charge

MIN_SELF_DELEGATION.name: MIN_SELF_DELEGATION
MIN_SELF_DELEGATION.comment: The minimum number of OSMO tokens that the operator must be staking with their own validator

RANK.name: RANK
RANK.comment: The rank of the validator in the validator set. Rank is determined by the number of OSMO tokens staked to the validator

MISSED_BLOCKS.name: MISSED_BLOCKS
MISSED_BLOCKS.comment: The number of blocks the validator has been down for during it's lifetime.

RAW_METADATA.name: RAW_METADATA
RAW_METADATA.comment: Additional details about the validator or token in json format.

_UNIQUE_KEY.name: _UNIQUE_KEY
_UNIQUE_KEY.comment: The unique key of the table

metadata.comment: Contains token metadata for assets on the Osmosis blockchain. This table was sourced from an API and may not contain every token.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: In this table, always Osmosis. Used to join to cross-chain tables. This column will deprecate in all tables except core.fact_blocks soon. Please modify your queries to join to the blocks table to use this field.

ADDRESS.name: ADDRESS
ADDRESS.comment: Address unique to an individual wallet, validator, or token.

CREATOR.name: CREATOR
CREATOR.comment: Name of the label creator - for now, this will always be "Flipside."

LABEL_TYPE.name: LABEL_TYPE
LABEL_TYPE.comment: A broad category that describes what a label is representing.

LABEL_SUBTYPE.name: LABEL_SUBTYPE
LABEL_SUBTYPE.comment: Adds more detail to the label type.

LABEL.name: LABEL
LABEL.comment: The label or name of the address.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the project the label belongs to.

ALIAS.name: ALIAS
ALIAS.comment: A secondary address for the token, where available

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

RAW_METADATA.name: RAW_METADATA
RAW_METADATA.comment: Additional details about the validator or token in json format.

has_stats.label: Has Stats?
has_stats.description: Indicates whether there are statistics for this table

metadata.name: FACT_TRANSACTIONS
metadata.comment: Records of all transactions that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. The columns blockchain, chain_id, and tx_status will be deprecating soon.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_FROM.name: TX_FROM
TX_FROM.comment: The wallet address of the individual who initiated the transaction

FEE.name: FEE
FEE.comment: The fee is paid by the initiator of the transaction. Fee = gas * gas price and is given in micro-OSMO.

GAS_USED.name: GAS_USED
GAS_USED.comment: The amount of gas consumed by the transaction.

GAS_WANTED.name: GAS_WANTED
GAS_WANTED.comment: Amount of gas requested for a transaction. It is provided by users when the transaction is generated.

TX_CODE.name: TX_CODE
TX_CODE.comment: A number that corresponds to various error codes. When "0", the transaction is successful. Non-zero numbers signify different types of transaction failures.

MSGS.name: MSGS
MSGS.comment: The underlying json from the messages or events within the transactions

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

metadata.name: TRANSFERS
metadata.comment: Records of all transfers on Osmosis, including IBC transfers as on- and off-ramps to Osmosis and wallet to wallet transfers

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TRANSFER_TYPE.name: TRANSFER_TYPE
TRANSFER_TYPE.comment: Details on the type of transfer occurring during the transaction. "IBC_Transfer_In" = depositing tokens onto Osmosis. "IBC_transfer_out" = withdrawing tokens from Osmosis. "Osmosis" = wallet to wallet transfer on Osmosis.

SENDER.name: SENDER
SENDER.comment: The wallet address of the individual sent tokens in the transfer.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

RECEIVER.name: RECEIVER
RECEIVER.comment: The wallet address of the individual received tokens in the transfer.

FOREIGN_ADDRESS.name: FOREIGN_ADDRESS
FOREIGN_ADDRESS.comment: The foreign address of the transfer if exists. This can be an IBC address or other non-IBC address

FOREIGN_CHAIN.name: FOREIGN_CHAIN
FOREIGN_CHAIN.comment: The name of the foreign chain transfer if exists

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

metadata.name: FACT_STAKING
metadata.comment: Records of all staking related transactions that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. These actions include delegate, undelegate, and redelegate. The columns blockchain, chain_id, and tx_status will be deprecating soon.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

TX_CALLER_ADDRESS.name: TX_CALLER_ADDRESS
TX_CALLER_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the individual who initiated the transaction.

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment:
<<<<<<< HEAD
Tells what action is happening in the transaction. I.E. is the user adding or removing liquidity to the pool. 
=======

>>>>>>> main

DELEGATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the individual who owns the delegated asset.

VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.name: VALIDATOR_ADDRESS
VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the validator related to the staking action.

REDELEGATE_SOURCE_VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.name: REDELEGATE_SOURCE_VALIDATOR_ADDRESS
REDELEGATE_SOURCE_VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the source alidator in a redelegation staking action.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

COMPLETION_TIME.name: COMPLETION_TIME
COMPLETION_TIME.comment: The time at which the undelegate or redelegate staking action is completed.

TX_CODE.name: TX_CODE

metadata.name: FACT_TRANSFERS
metadata.comment: Records of all transfers on Osmosis, including IBC transfers as on- and off-ramps to Osmosis and wallet to wallet transfers. The columns blockchain, chain_id, and tx_status will be deprecating soon.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

TRANSFER_TYPE.name: TRANSFER_TYPE
TRANSFER_TYPE.comment: Details on the type of transfer occurring during the transaction. "IBC_Transfer_In" = depositing tokens onto Osmosis. "IBC_transfer_out" = withdrawing tokens from Osmosis. "Osmosis" = wallet to wallet transfer on Osmosis.

SENDER.name: SENDER
SENDER.comment: The wallet address of the individual sent tokens in the transfer.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

RECEIVER.name: RECEIVER
RECEIVER.comment: The wallet address of the individual received tokens in the transfer.

FOREIGN_ADDRESS.name: FOREIGN_ADDRESS
FOREIGN_ADDRESS.comment: The foreign address of the transfer if exists. This can be an IBC address or other non-IBC address

FOREIGN_CHAIN.name: FOREIGN_CHAIN
FOREIGN_CHAIN.comment: The name of the foreign chain transfer if exists

metadata.name: GOVERNANCE_PROPOSAL_DEPOSITS
metadata.comment: Records of all proposal deposits that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. At least 500 OSMO must be deposited for a proposal to be voted on.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

DEPOSITOR.name: DEPOSITOR
DEPOSITOR.comment: The wallet address of the individual who deposited funds into the proposal. At least 500 OSMO must be deposited into a proposal after it is submitted for it to go to vote.

PROPOSAL_ID.name: PROPOSAL_ID
PROPOSAL_ID.comment: Numeric ID that corresponds to the proposal.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

metadata.name: EZ_POOL_HOUR
metadata.comment: The table is an hourly summary of each pool within Osmosis. The table is currently limited to show at most four tokens. For pools that contain more than four tokens, those tokens are omitted.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

POOL_ID.name: POOL_ID
POOL_ID.comment: Identifier for the pool within the module

TOKEN_0_CURRENCY.name: TOKEN_0_CURRENCY
TOKEN_0_CURRENCY.comment: The first token address contained within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_0_SYMBOL.name: TOKEN_0_SYMBOL
TOKEN_0_SYMBOL.comment: The token symbol of first token address contained within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_0_AMOUNT.name: TOKEN_0_AMOUNT
TOKEN_0_AMOUNT.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of the first token within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_1_CURRENCY.name: TOKEN_1_CURRENCY
TOKEN_1_CURRENCY.comment: The second token address contained within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_1_SYMBOL.name: TOKEN_1_SYMBOL
TOKEN_1_SYMBOL.comment: The token symbol of second token address contained within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_1_AMOUNT.name: TOKEN_1_AMOUNT
TOKEN_1_AMOUNT.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of the second token within this liquidity pool

PRICE.name: PRICE
PRICE.comment: The price of the first token as denominated in the token_1_currency. This only applies to two-token pools where one of the tokens is osmos

PRICE_USD.name: PRICE_USD
PRICE_USD.comment: The price of the token in USD

TWAP.name: TWAP
TWAP.comment: The time weighted asset price, denominated in osmos. This is calculated by averaging the high, low, open, and close of the day

TWAP_USD.name: TWAP_USD
TWAP_USD.comment: The time weighted asset price, denominated in USD. This is calculated by averaging the high, low, open, and close of the day

LIQUIDITY.name: LIQUIDITY
LIQUIDITY.comment: The total value of tokens within the pool, denominated in osmos

LIQUIDITY_USD.name: LIQUIDITY_USD
LIQUIDITY_USD.comment: The total value of tokens within the pool, denominated in osmos

VOLUME.name: VOLUME
VOLUME.comment: The total value of tokens swapped in and out of the pool, denominated in osmos

VOLUME_USD.name: VOLUME_USD
VOLUME_USD.comment: The total value of tokens swapped in and out of the pool, denominated in USD

metadata.name: STAKING_REWARDS
metadata.comment: Records of all claimed rewards earned from staking that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. These actions include claim and withdrawal_rewards.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_CALLER_ADDRESS.name: TX_CALLER_ADDRESS
TX_CALLER_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the individual who initiated the transaction.

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment:
<<<<<<< HEAD
Tells what action is happening in the transaction. I.E. is the user adding or removing liquidity to the pool. 
=======
The action taken in the msg group. For staking this includes delegate, undelegate, redelegate, withdraw_rewards.
>>>>>>> main

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Numeric value grouping different messages together to represent a single action.  NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

DELEGATOR_ADDRESS.name: DELEGATOR_ADDRESS
DELEGATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the individual who owns the delegated asset.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.name: VALIDATOR_ADDRESS
VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the validator related to the staking action.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

metadata.name: FACT_LOCKED_LIQUIDITY_ACTIONS
metadata.comment: Includes all actions related to locked LP tokens. The columns blockchain, chain_id, and tx_status will be deprecating soon.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Value grouping different messages together to represent a single action. Format will include the numeric msg_group and msg_sub_group with a ":" seperator. The subgroup will always be 0 except for "Exec" actions. NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_ACTION.name: MSG_ACTION
MSG_ACTION.comment: The attribute value when the message type = 'mesage' and the attribute key = 'action'

MSG_ACTION_DESCRIPTION.name: MSG_ACTION_DESCRIPTION
MSG_ACTION_DESCRIPTION.comment: A user friendly description of what action occured

LOCKER_ADDRESS.name: LOCKER_ADDRESS
LOCKER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of user that performed an action related to locked lp tokens

LOCK_ID.name: LOCK_ID
LOCK_ID.comment: The unique id related to the specifc address, pool, and lock duration

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

POOL_ID.name: POOL_ID
POOL_ID.comment: Identifier for the pool within the module

LOCK_DURATION.name: LOCK_DURATION
LOCK_DURATION.comment: The length of time the LP toke takes to unlock

UNLOCK_TIME.name: UNLOCK_TIME
UNLOCK_TIME.comment: When the LP token is fully unlocked and liquid again

IS_SUPERFLUID.name: IS_SUPERFLUID
IS_SUPERFLUID.comment: The length of time the LP toke takes to unlock

UNPOOL_NEW_LOCK_IDS.name: UNPOOL_NEW_LOCK_IDS
UNPOOL_NEW_LOCK_IDS.comment: The new lock ids generated when a lp position is unpooled

metadata.name: BLOCKS
metadata.comment: Records of all blocks that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

CHAIN_ID.name: CHAIN_ID
CHAIN_ID.comment: The name and version of the blockchain. This column will deprecate in all tables except core.fact_blocks soon. Please modify your queries to join to the blocks table to use this field.

TX_COUNT.name: TX_COUNT
TX_COUNT.comment: The number of transactions that occurred during a block.

PROPOSER_ADDRESS.name: PROPOSER_ADDRESS
PROPOSER_ADDRESS.comment: The address of the validator that proposed the block.

VALIDATOR_HASH.name: VALIDATOR_HASH
VALIDATOR_HASH.comment: The root hash of the new validator set.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: In this table, always Osmosis. Used to join to cross-chain tables. This column will deprecate in all tables except core.fact_blocks soon. Please modify your queries to join to the blocks table to use this field.

ADDRESS.name: ADDRESS
ADDRESS.comment: Address unique to an individual wallet, validator, or token.

CREATOR.name: CREATOR
CREATOR.comment: Name of the label creator - for now, this will always be "Flipside."

LABEL_TYPE.name: LABEL_TYPE
LABEL_TYPE.comment: A broad category that describes what a label is representing.

LABEL_SUBTYPE.name: LABEL_SUBTYPE
LABEL_SUBTYPE.comment: Adds more detail to the label type.

LABEL.name: LABEL
LABEL.comment: The label or name of the address.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the project the label belongs to.

ALIAS.name: ALIAS
ALIAS.comment: A secondary address for the token, where available

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

RAW_METADATA.name: RAW_METADATA
RAW_METADATA.comment: Additional details about the validator or token in json format.

MEMO.comment: The memo the user input into the transaction body

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

BALANCE_TYPE.comment: Either "staked" or "liquid" corresponding to how the currency is in the wallet.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL

BALANCE.name: BALANCE

metadata.name: EZ_REDBANK_REWARD_CLAIMS
metadata.comment: Records of all reward claim actions that occured within MARS red bank on osmosis

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Value grouping different messages together to represent a single action. Format will include the numeric msg_group and msg_sub_group with a ":" seperator. The subgroup will always be 0 except for "Exec" actions. NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_SUB_GROUP.name: MSG_SUB_GROUP
MSG_SUB_GROUP.comment: Silver only -- Numeric value grouping different messages together to represent a single action within a group. This is relevent for exec actions that contain mutiple underlying actions. NULL sub group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_INDEX.name: MSG_INDEX
MSG_INDEX.comment: Short for "message index," the position in which messages occur in a transaction.

CONTRACT_NAME.name: CONTRACT_NAME
CONTRACT_NAME.comment: The name of the contract that was interacted with

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment: The action that took place in the transaction. This will always be claim_rewards.

USER.name: USER
USER.comment: The address that the reward claim is relevant for

MARS_REWARDS.name: MARS_REWARDS
MARS_REWARDS.comment: The amount of rewards that were claimed

metadata.name: FACT_VALIDATORS
metadata.comment: Contains validator metadata for assets on the Osmosis blockchain. This table was sourced from an API and may not contain every token.

ADDRESS.name: ADDRESS
ADDRESS.comment: Address unique to an individual wallet, validator, or token.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: In this table, always Osmosis. Used to join to cross-chain tables. This column will deprecate in all tables except core.fact_blocks soon. Please modify your queries to join to the blocks table to use this field.

CREATOR.name: CREATOR
CREATOR.comment: Name of the label creator - for now, this will always be "Flipside."

LABEL_TYPE.name: LABEL_TYPE
LABEL_TYPE.comment: A broad category that describes what a label is representing.

LABEL_SUBTYPE.name: LABEL_SUBTYPE
LABEL_SUBTYPE.comment: Adds more detail to the label type.

LABEL.name: LABEL
LABEL.comment: The label or name of the address.

PROJECT_NAME.name: PROJECT_NAME
PROJECT_NAME.comment: The name of the project the label belongs to.

ACCOUNT_ADDRESS.name: ACCOUNT_ADDRESS
ACCOUNT_ADDRESS.comment: The osmosis address of the user / entity that operates the validator.

DELEGATOR_SHARES.name: DELEGATOR_SHARES
DELEGATOR_SHARES.comment: The number of tokens staked to the validator.

RANK.name: RANK

MISSED_BLOCKS.name: MISSED_BLOCKS
MISSED_BLOCKS.comment: The number of blocks the validator has been down for during it's lifetime.

RAW_METADATA.name: RAW_METADATA
RAW_METADATA.comment: Additional details about the validator or token in json format.

metadata.name: MSGS
metadata.comment: Records of all messages associated to transactions that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Numeric value grouping different messages together to represent a single action.  NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_SUB_GROUP.name: MSG_SUB_GROUP
MSG_SUB_GROUP.comment: Silver only -- Numeric value grouping different messages together to represent a single action within a group. This is relevent for exec actions that contain mutiple underlying actions. NULL sub group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_INDEX.name: MSG_INDEX
MSG_INDEX.comment: Short for "message index," the position in which messages occur in a transaction.

MSG_TYPE.name: MSG_TYPE
MSG_TYPE.comment: A string containing information about the type of message occurring.

MSG.name: MSG
MSG.comment: The underlying json from the message or event within the transactions

metadata.name: STAKING
metadata.comment: Records of all staking related transactions that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. These actions include delegate, undelegate, and redelegate.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_CALLER_ADDRESS.name: TX_CALLER_ADDRESS
TX_CALLER_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the individual who initiated the transaction.

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment:
<<<<<<< HEAD
Tells what action is happening in the transaction. I.E. is the user adding or removing liquidity to the pool. 
=======
The action taken in the msg group. For staking this includes delegate, undelegate, redelegate, withdraw_rewards.
>>>>>>> main

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Numeric value grouping different messages together to represent a single action.  NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_SUB_GROUP.name: MSG_SUB_GROUP
MSG_SUB_GROUP.comment: Silver only -- Numeric value grouping different messages together to represent a single action within a group. This is relevent for exec actions that contain mutiple underlying actions. NULL sub group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

DELEGATOR_ADDRESS.name: DELEGATOR_ADDRESS
DELEGATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the individual who owns the delegated asset.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.name: VALIDATOR_ADDRESS
VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the validator related to the staking action.

REDELEGATE_SOURCE_VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.name: REDELEGATE_SOURCE_VALIDATOR_ADDRESS
REDELEGATE_SOURCE_VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the source alidator in a redelegation staking action.

COMPLETION_TIME.name: COMPLETION_TIME
COMPLETION_TIME.comment: The time at which the undelegate or redelegate staking action is completed.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

metadata.comment: Records of all votes on proposals. The columns blockchain, chain_id, and tx_status will be deprecating soon.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

VOTER.name: VOTER
VOTER.comment: Address of the delegator that voted on the proposal.

PROPOSAL_ID.name: PROPOSAL_ID
PROPOSAL_ID.comment: Numeric ID that corresponds to the proposal.

VOTE_OPTION.name: VOTE_OPTION
VOTE_OPTION.comment: How the delegator voted on the proposal.

MEMO.name: MEMO
MEMO.comment: The memo the user input into the transaction body

metadata.name: FACT_SUPERFLUID_STAKING
metadata.comment: Records of all staking related transactions that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. These actions include delegate, undelegate, and redelegate. The columns blockchain, chain_id, and tx_status will be deprecating soon.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment:
<<<<<<< HEAD
Tells what action is happening in the transaction. I.E. is the user adding or removing liquidity to the pool. 
=======
The action taken in the msg group. For staking this includes delegate, undelegate, redelegate, withdraw_rewards.
>>>>>>> main

DELEGATOR_ADDRESS.name: DELEGATOR_ADDRESS
DELEGATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the individual who owns the delegated asset.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the amount by POW(10, decimal) to get the amount used in the transaction. This value can be NULL, as decimals are hand curated from an outside source and not found on-chain.

VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.name: VALIDATOR_ADDRESS
VALIDATOR_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the validator related to the staking action.

LOCK_ID.name: LOCK_ID
LOCK_ID.comment: An ID corresponding to the locking step of the transaction.

IS_UNPOOL.name: IS_UNPOOL
IS_UNPOOL.comment: Boolean value indicating whether the transaction is an unpool action.

metadata.name: RED_BANK_ACTIONS
metadata.comment: Records of all collateral and debt actions taken using MARS red bank on osmosis

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Value grouping different messages together to represent a single action. Format will include the numeric msg_group and msg_sub_group with a ":" seperator. The subgroup will always be 0 except for "Exec" actions. NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_SUB_GROUP.name: MSG_SUB_GROUP
MSG_SUB_GROUP.comment: Silver only -- Numeric value grouping different messages together to represent a single action within a group. This is relevent for exec actions that contain mutiple underlying actions. NULL sub group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_INDEX.name: MSG_INDEX
MSG_INDEX.comment: Short for "message index," the position in which messages occur in a transaction.

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

metadata.name: FACT_POOL_HOUR
metadata.comment: The table is an hourly summary of each pool within Osmosis. The table is currently limited to show at most four tokens. For pools that contain more than four tokens, those tokens are omitted.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

POOL_ID.name: POOL_ID
POOL_ID.comment: Identifier for the pool within the module

TOKEN_0_CURRENCY.name: TOKEN_0_CURRENCY
TOKEN_0_CURRENCY.comment: The first token address contained within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_0_AMOUNT.name: TOKEN_0_AMOUNT
TOKEN_0_AMOUNT.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of the first token within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_1_CURRENCY.name: TOKEN_1_CURRENCY
TOKEN_1_CURRENCY.comment: The second token address contained within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_1_AMOUNT.name: TOKEN_1_AMOUNT
TOKEN_1_AMOUNT.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of the second token within this liquidity pool

PRICE.name: PRICE
PRICE.comment: The price of the first token as denominated in the token_1_currency. This only applies to two-token pools where one of the tokens is osmos

PRICE_USD.name: PRICE_USD
PRICE_USD.comment: The price of the token in USD

TWAP.name: TWAP
TWAP.comment: The time weighted asset price, denominated in osmos. This is calculated by averaging the high, low, open, and close of the day

TWAP_USD.name: TWAP_USD
TWAP_USD.comment: The time weighted asset price, denominated in USD. This is calculated by averaging the high, low, open, and close of the day

LIQUIDITY.name: LIQUIDITY
LIQUIDITY.comment: The total value of tokens within the pool, denominated in osmos

LIQUIDITY_USD.name: LIQUIDITY_USD
LIQUIDITY_USD.comment: The total value of tokens within the pool, denominated in osmos

VOLUME.name: VOLUME
VOLUME.comment: The total value of tokens swapped in and out of the pool, denominated in osmos

VOLUME_USD.name: VOLUME_USD
VOLUME_USD.comment: The total value of tokens swapped in and out of the pool, denominated in USD

TOKEN_2_CURRENCY.name: TOKEN_2_CURRENCY
TOKEN_2_CURRENCY.comment: The third token address contained within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_2_AMOUNT.name: TOKEN_2_AMOUNT
TOKEN_2_AMOUNT.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of the third token within this liquidity pool (if exists)

TOKEN_3_CURRENCY.name: TOKEN_3_CURRENCY
TOKEN_3_CURRENCY.comment: The fourth token address contained within this liquidity pool

TOKEN_3_AMOUNT.name: TOKEN_3_AMOUNT
TOKEN_3_AMOUNT.comment: The decimal adjusted amount of the fourth token within this liquidity pool (if exists)

metadata.name: FACT_VALIDATOR_COMMISSION
metadata.comment: Information about all validator commission that have been claimed on Axelar.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

TX_CALLER_ADDRESS.name: TX_CALLER_ADDRESS
TX_CALLER_ADDRESS.comment: The wallet address of the individual who initiated the transaction.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Value grouping different messages together to represent a single action. Format will include the numeric msg_group and msg_sub_group with a ":" seperator. The subgroup will always be 0 except for "Exec" actions. NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount of tokens in the staking action

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

VALIDATOR_ADDRESS_OPERATOR.name: VALIDATOR_ADDRESS_OPERATOR
VALIDATOR_ADDRESS_OPERATOR.comment: The wallet address of the validator related to the staking action.

VALIDATOR_ADDRESS_REWARD.name: VALIDATOR_ADDRESS_REWARD
VALIDATOR_ADDRESS_REWARD.comment: The wallet address that recieves the commissiion of the validator.

metadata.name: LOCKED_LIQUIDITY_ACTIONS_BEGIN_UNLOCK
metadata.comment: Records of all LP token locking transactions that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. These actions include lock, unlock, unpool, and all superfluid actions.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Value grouping different messages together to represent a single action. Format will include the numeric msg_group and msg_sub_group with a ":" seperator. The subgroup will always be 0 except for "Exec" actions. NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_TYPE.name: MSG_TYPE
MSG_TYPE.comment: A string containing information about the type of message occurring.

LOCK_ID.name: LOCK_ID
LOCK_ID.comment: The unique id related to the specifc address, pool, and lock duration

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

LOCKER.name: LOCKER
LOCKER.comment: The address of user that performed an action related to locked lp tokens

UNLOCK_TIME.name: UNLOCK_TIME
UNLOCK_TIME.comment: When the LP token is fully unlocked and liquid again

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The time the block was inserted into to the Flipside database.

metadata.name: FACT_SWAPS
metadata.comment: Records of all transactions that have occurred on Osmosis, dating back to the genesis block. The columns blockchain, chain_id, and tx_status will be deprecating soon.

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

TRADER.name: TRADER

FROM_AMOUNT.name: FROM_AMOUNT

FROM_CURRENCY.name: FROM_CURRENCY
FROM_CURRENCY.comment: The currency that the user sent to be swapped for another currency.

FROM_DECIMAL.name: FROM_DECIMAL
FROM_DECIMAL.comment: Divide the swap_from_amount by POW(10, swap_from_decimal) to get the amount the user swapped.

TO_AMOUNT.name: TO_AMOUNT
TO_AMOUNT.comment: The amount that the user sent to be swapped for another currency.

TO_CURRENCY.name: TO_CURRENCY
TO_CURRENCY.comment: The currency that the user sent to be swapped for another currency.

TO_DECIMAL.name: TO_DECIMAL
TO_DECIMAL.comment: Divide the swap_to_amount by POW(10, swap_to_decimal) to get the amount the user received.

POOL_IDS.comment: Identifier for the pool within the module

TX_STATUS.name: TX_STATUS

TRADER.name: TRADER

FROM_AMOUNT.name: FROM_AMOUNT

FROM_CURRENCY.name: FROM_CURRENCY

FROM_DECIMAL.name: FROM_DECIMAL
FROM_DECIMAL.comment: Divide the swap_from_amount by POW(10, swap_from_decimal) to get the amount the user swapped.

TO_AMOUNT.name: TO_AMOUNT
TO_AMOUNT.comment: The amount that the user sent to be swapped for another currency.

TO_CURRENCY.name: TO_CURRENCY

TO_DECIMAL.name: TO_DECIMAL
TO_DECIMAL.comment: Divide the swap_to_amount by POW(10, swap_to_decimal) to get the amount the user received.

metadata.name: EZ_REDBANK_REWARD_DISTRIBUTIONS
metadata.comment: Records of all reward claim actions that occured within MARS red bank on osmosis

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction was successful, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

MSG_GROUP.name: MSG_GROUP
MSG_GROUP.comment: Value grouping different messages together to represent a single action. Format will include the numeric msg_group and msg_sub_group with a ":" seperator. The subgroup will always be 0 except for "Exec" actions. NULL group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_SUB_GROUP.name: MSG_SUB_GROUP
MSG_SUB_GROUP.comment: Silver only -- Numeric value grouping different messages together to represent a single action within a group. This is relevent for exec actions that contain mutiple underlying actions. NULL sub group means messages are related to the header (overall transaction)

MSG_INDEX.name: MSG_INDEX
MSG_INDEX.comment: Short for "message index," the position in which messages occur in a transaction.

CONTRACT_NAME.name: CONTRACT_NAME
CONTRACT_NAME.comment: The name of the contract that was interacted with

ACTION.name: ACTION
ACTION.comment: The action that took place in the transaction. This will always be distribute_rewards.

TO_ADDRESS.name: TO_ADDRESS
TO_ADDRESS.comment: The address that the distribution went to

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount of token that was distributed

metadata.name: ADDRESS_TAGS
metadata.comment: Holds data for our address tags.

BLOCKCHAIN.name: BLOCKCHAIN
BLOCKCHAIN.comment: The blockchain that the address belongs to.

CREATOR.name: CREATOR
CREATOR.comment: Who created the tag. 'flipside' for official flipside tags.

ADDRESS.name: ADDRESS
ADDRESS.comment: The address of the contract or wallet the tag describes.

START_DATE.name: START_DATE
START_DATE.comment: Date the tag first applies. For tags that are permanent, this might be the date the address had its first behavior that warrants its tag, or the addresses' first transaction.

END_DATE.name: END_DATE
END_DATE.comment: Date the tag no longer applies (for tags that are permanent or currently active, end_date can be NULL).

TAG_CREATED_AT.name: TAG_CREATED_AT
TAG_CREATED_AT.comment: Date the tag was added to our data.

metadata.name: TRANSFERS
metadata.comment: Records of all transfers on Axelar, including IBC transfers as on- and off-ramps to Axelar and wallet to wallet transfers

BLOCK_ID.name: BLOCK_ID
BLOCK_ID.comment: The block height the block was recorded at.

BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.name: BLOCK_TIMESTAMP
BLOCK_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block began.

TX_ID.name: TX_ID
TX_ID.comment: A unique key that identifies a transaction. Called "TxHash" on block explorers.

TX_SUCCEEDED.name: TX_SUCCEEDED
TX_SUCCEEDED.comment: Transaction status is "TRUE" if the transaction went through, "FALSE" if the transaction failed.

TRANSFER_TYPE.name: TRANSFER_TYPE
TRANSFER_TYPE.comment: Details on the type of transfer occurring during the transaction. "Transfer_In" = depositing tokens onto Axelar. "Transfer_out" = withdrawing tokens from Axelar. "Axelar" = wallet to wallet transfer on Axelar.

SENDER.name: SENDER
SENDER.comment: The wallet address of the individual sent tokens in the transfer.

AMOUNT.name: AMOUNT
AMOUNT.comment: The amount that was used in the transaction message.

CURRENCY.name: CURRENCY
CURRENCY.comment: The currency that was used in the transaction message.

DECIMAL.name: DECIMAL
DECIMAL.comment: Divide the raw amount of currency as provided in the amount column by the decimal to get the actual amount in AXL or other currency.

RECEIVER.name: RECEIVER
RECEIVER.comment: The wallet address of the individual received tokens in the transfer.

FOREIGN_ADDRESS.name: FOREIGN_ADDRESS
FOREIGN_ADDRESS.comment: The foreign address of the transfer if exists. This can be an IBC address or other non-IBC address

FOREIGN_CHAIN.name: FOREIGN_CHAIN
FOREIGN_CHAIN.comment: The name of the foreign chain transfer if exists

_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.name: _INSERTED_TIMESTAMP
_INSERTED_TIMESTAMP.comment: The date and time at which the block or transaction was inserted in the bronze tables.
